Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.46,0:00:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I first became aware inside a coin locker…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in pitch-black darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.97,0:00:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.60,0:00:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue of the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.40,0:00:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The blue of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.94,0:00:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the blue windowpane.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.28,0:00:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunther Milch
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.67,0:00:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,was arrested in 1988 for\Nthe robbery of a Bayern-Basf armored car.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.63,0:00:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He was sent to Badenburg Prison\Nto serve time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.80,0:00:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1991, he broke out of that prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.05,0:00:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He spent six months using a nail
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.10,0:00:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sharpened into a file\Nto cut through a steel grate.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.01,0:00:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days later, he was captured.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.93,0:00:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, he was sent to Kreiner Prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.06,0:01:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,But in 1993, he escaped through\Nthe sewer pipes of the toilets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.36,0:01:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,His sewage-stained prison clothes were\Ndiscovered at a nearby river.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.36,0:01:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He was then arrested for attempted robbery
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.49,0:01:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of a Maximillian Co.\Npayroll delivery truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.86,0:01:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1997, while at Ingeborg Prison,\Nhe spent one and a half years
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.62,0:01:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,digging a tunnel from the showers\Nwith a spoon and escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.71,0:01:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The toilets here really stink!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.04,0:01:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I've crawled through sewers,\Nso I know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.63,0:01:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up and walk!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.27,0:01:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-What a gloomy dude.\N-Face forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.10,0:01:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that that Dr. Tenma guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.98,0:01:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Get walking!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.07,0:01:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought he'd look\Nso darn hopeless and pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.58,0:03:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask you one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.66,0:03:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,As for the 1986 poisoning murders\Nat Eisler Memorial Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.33,0:03:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of Director Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Director of Surgery Oppenheimer,\Nand Dr. Boyer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.09,0:03:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,you deny any involvement at all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Since this interrogation began,\Nyou haven't uttered a single word.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut the crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.19,0:03:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, is this really what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.52,0:03:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If you remain silent, we'll press charges
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll never win in court.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.16,0:04:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Talk to us. You'll feel better\Nif you tell us everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.12,0:04:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? What's the commotion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.21,0:04:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Milch has terrible stomach pain!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.21,0:04:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor! Dr. Durer!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.51,0:04:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Dr. Durer?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.43,0:04:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in the interrogation room now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.51,0:04:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy Peter drank cleaning fluid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.48,0:04:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,-You think he's choking on his vomit?\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.15,0:04:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I… can't breathe…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.74,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,For Christ's sake.\NGuess we'll just have to get that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.91,0:04:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.53,0:04:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you have a look at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.38,0:04:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it hurt here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.80,0:05:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.39,0:05:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring me hot water\Nas well as towels and fresh clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.68,0:05:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to leave!\NYou could catch what he's got!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you faking an illness?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.58,0:05:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, cut me a little slack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the first doctor\Nwho's seen through my act so quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to get sent to the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.76,0:05:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,where I'd have\Na better chance of escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.59,0:05:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how I pulled off\Nthat armored truck robbery?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.43,0:05:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I jumped in front of the truck\Nacting like I was sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.39,0:05:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When the security guards\Njumped out in a panic,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.89,0:05:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,my buddy showed up with his gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.61,0:05:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never killed anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.28,0:05:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Unlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.82,0:06:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it? Want to escape with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.95,0:06:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so darn gloomy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.71,0:06:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how you end up looking\Nin a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.83,0:06:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand\Ntiny little places like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.71,0:06:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I first became aware inside a coin locker…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in pitch-black darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.64,0:06:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,While my mom and dad worked,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.60,0:06:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,they stuck me inside\Nwhere I waited forever for them to return.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.69,0:06:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"Let's go to Tunisia someday."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.15,0:06:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom and dad would always say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.03,0:06:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad said one time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.53,0:06:48.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"If work today goes well,\Nwe're going to Tunisia!"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.25,0:06:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But three days later,\Nthey still haven't returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.46,0:06:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom and dad probably left me…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.84,0:07:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and went to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.09,0:07:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll get out of this tiny joint
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.39,0:07:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and go to Tunisia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.23,0:07:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What a gloomy look.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.36,0:07:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There's zero hope in your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.32,0:07:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You lack the hope that I've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.36,0:07:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do when you're caught again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.91,0:07:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just escape again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.62,0:07:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep escaping over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.46,0:07:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose\Nyou'll just be silent again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.88,0:07:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.97,0:07:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,While we're here,\Nterrible things will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.60,0:07:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So I must tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.22,0:07:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.64,0:07:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe what I tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.56,0:07:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But I must fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.56,0:08:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Over and over again,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.36,0:08:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I must tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.70,0:08:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We sentence the defendant\Nto 20 years imprisonment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When my father was found guilty,\Nmy path in life was decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.38,0:08:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,After the war, my father moved from\NSudetenland in Czechoslovakia to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.34,0:08:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1949, he started a small radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.34,0:08:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But during the Cold War in the 60's,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.35,0:08:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,my father was arrested for spying
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and for the murder of\Na Bundestag member's secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.85,0:08:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It sent shock waves to the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.56,0:08:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My father pleaded innocent\Nbut was sentenced to 20 years in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother continued to insist\Non his innocence but died in 1971.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.45,0:08:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1972, my father died from grief,\Nstill imprisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.79,0:09:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1973, while I was in secondary school,\Nmy father was proven innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.00,0:09:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,After I graduated\Nfrom Düsseldorf University,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.51,0:09:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I joined Hoffman Law, a major law firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In my first case,\Nmy client was found innocent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.22,0:09:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I proved they'd been falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I continued to help\Nclients who had been falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.35,0:09:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Fritz Verdemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,went from being the "son of a spy"\Nto the darling of the legal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,"Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.83,0:09:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's radio station would\Nstart every day with this song
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.50,0:09:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and end with it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.34,0:09:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.13,0:09:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For you who lived in East Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.63,0:09:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't this song symbolize the free world?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.26,0:09:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.34,0:09:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My father maintained his innocence\Nuntil his dying breath in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.60,0:09:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To honor his memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.64,0:10:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to take\Nany case where it's possible
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.69,0:10:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that the defendant\Nmay have been falsely accused.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.73,0:10:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me everything you know\Nabout Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.74,0:10:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Ilsa, how did the prenatal exam go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.87,0:10:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything's coming along fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.67,0:10:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They said I could give birth at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.79,0:10:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You passed a man in the lobby, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Is he the man you told me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.01,0:10:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's Alfred Baul.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.55,0:10:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,He asked me to join him\Nin defending Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.14,0:10:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you turn down\NDr. Tenma's case the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.31,0:10:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who asked me\Nto take the case was Hans Georg Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.61,0:10:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It made no sense at all why\Na mogul like him was asking me
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.99,0:10:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to take his case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.24,0:10:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But this time, the reason is very clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.83,0:11:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Baul has come to me on behalf
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.12,0:11:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of former patients of Dr. Tenma\Nwhose lives he saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.17,0:11:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.30,0:11:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's quite clear to me
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.59,0:11:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that this Dr. Tenma\Nwas a magnificent doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.43,0:11:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You should take the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.93,0:11:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If I win, I'd get paid a bundle\Nin contingency fees by that mogul.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.02,0:11:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But those patients\Nwon't be able to pay much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.19,0:11:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you chose cases\Nbased on how much you'd be paid,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.94,0:11:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd have a much larger law firm by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.16,0:11:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's "Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,-Turn it off.\N-Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:11:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.84,0:11:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, why don't we go out\Nand get some dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.39,0:12:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,For the sake of the baby in your belly,\Nyou've got to eat for two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.98,0:12:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's for sure.\NThe baby always kicks when it's hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.65,0:12:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, honey, what restaurant\Nwould you like to dine at?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.49,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see. How about that one place?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.58,0:12:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he disappeared into the raging fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.92,0:12:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the last time I saw Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.18,0:12:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like me to start\Nat the beginning again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.35,0:12:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell it over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.10,0:12:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll keep telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.89,0:12:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the fourth one I've told.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.44,0:12:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Four lawyers have come to interview me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.82,0:12:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But all they've said is,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.73,0:13:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Plead guilty to some of the crimes\Nto get a lighter sentence."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.99,0:13:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's no surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It sounds to me that instead\Nof insisting on your innocence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.83,0:13:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to prove that\Nthis young man Johan exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.67,0:13:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.96,0:13:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you don't need a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.51,0:13:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.68,0:13:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What was the real start of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.39,0:13:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, a young boy shot in the head\Nwas brought to the hospital--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.48,0:13:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No. There must have been something\Nthat happened before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A Turkish woman…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me back my husband!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.03,0:13:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,People's lives aren't created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.37,0:13:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All human lives are created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.17,0:13:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,whether what I did was right or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.22,0:14:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell if a patient is good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.30,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My crime…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My crime was saving that young boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.10,0:14:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.02,0:14:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.10,0:14:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,does a doctor have the right to choose
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.23,0:14:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,whether to save someone\Ndepending on if they're good or evil?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.11,0:14:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.28,0:14:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,They are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.11,0:14:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know… I still can't decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.95,0:14:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same with us lawyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.12,0:14:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't tell\Nif a defendant is good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.88,0:14:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a list of the people\Nwho have asked me to represent you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.13,0:14:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael Hotter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Stephen Kramp.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.72,0:14:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Kiefer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.39,0:14:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Rudolf Hubert.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess Mr. Kiefer\Nand Mr. Hubert are doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Horst Henschel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.23,0:14:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Harmut Hesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hesse too, huh? I hope\Nhe's enjoying life with his grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.95,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Time's up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I'm glad to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.21,0:15:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.38,0:15:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take your case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.84,0:15:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawyers also cannot tell\Nif someone is good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.68,0:15:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one thing we must do\Nwhen defending a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.76,0:15:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.15,0:15:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I said give me another!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.23,0:15:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am, I don't think--
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.61,0:15:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When did this place stop\Nletting me order drinks?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.16,0:15:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.17,0:15:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You laughed just now, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.46,0:16:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You did laugh!\NYou looked at me and laughed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.67,0:16:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I know who you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.14,0:16:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You always used to\Ncome to our place groveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.14,0:16:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the assistant manager\Nat the Nordhein-West Bank!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.85,0:16:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give that look!\NYou should be happy I'm back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.65,0:16:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know\Nthat Eva Heinemann is back in Düsseldorf.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.91,0:16:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for this important information,\NDr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.33,0:16:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been trying to contact you\Never since I heard
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that you took up Dr. Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry I couldn't answer your calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.54,0:16:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been running around\Ninterviewing people.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.71,0:16:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Interviewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.13,0:16:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Dr. Tenma's former patients\Nare backing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.14,0:16:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.60,0:16:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,They say Dr. Tenma's a magnificent doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.35,0:16:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And have you gotten any useful evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.02,0:17:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.35,0:17:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I was hoping to get a statement\Nthat proved Dr. Tenma's alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.11,0:17:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The only way to prove\NDr. Tenma's innocence is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.95,0:17:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to prove the existence of Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.49,0:17:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,-Dr. Reichwein.\N-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.04,0:17:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That part of Dr. Tenma's story\Nwhen he tried to shoot Johan,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.46,0:17:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to keep quiet about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.13,0:17:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? But that is the only part of\Nhis story that can prove that Johan--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether Johan exists or not,\NTenma is still innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.18,0:17:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now listen, Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.01,0:17:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in this country\Nmerely want a scapegoat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.94,0:17:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife and I will have a child soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.90,0:17:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a truly just world for our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.86,0:17:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Judges and prosecutors pin crimes\Non innocent people
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.36,0:17:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,just so they can end cases quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:18:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is for this country\Nrepents for its lack of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.62,0:18:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Reichwein.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.54,0:18:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.63,0:18:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm looking for a certain person now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.46,0:18:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This woman just might know\Nsomething very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.64,0:18:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.31,0:18:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma's former fiancée, Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Dr. Reichwein?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-She's here.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.61,0:18:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,She came with me here to this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.03,0:18:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Every damn one of them laughed at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.08,0:18:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They looked at me and laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva, aren't you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, dammit! Don't be so annoying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.80,0:18:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Go meet this lawyer, for Tenma's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.93,0:18:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.05,0:19:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what I told you before?\NI tried to shoot and kill that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.06,0:19:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was shocked when you told me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.98,0:19:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But you didn't shoot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.57,0:19:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. I didn't shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.32,0:19:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.61,0:19:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't have him die on me yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.70,0:19:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't about to let that jerk\Nwho ruined my life die that easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.41,0:19:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have him sent to prison forever\Nand regret what he did his whole life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.84,0:19:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll regret dumping me forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.23,0:19:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She's passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.92,0:20:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? Did you have a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.43,0:20:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There were… three shots…\NBut I didn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I… didn't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.56,0:20:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There was… a blonde man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.90,0:20:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva did you…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.40,0:20:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,see Johan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.53,0:20:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A song that symbolizes\Nthe free world, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.62,0:20:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann, your wife's\Nin labor and is headed to the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.21,0:20:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? She is?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Klinger, contact Mr. Baul immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.67,0:20:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.97,0:21:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him I'm sorry but he'll have\Nto interview Dr. Tenma for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.64,0:21:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nice to meet you.\NI am Baul, a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.14,0:21:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be taking care\Nof your interview today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How have things been?\NAre you sleeping well?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.82,0:21:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Oops!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be right-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.74,0:21:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think I'll ever\Nget used to writing with my left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.45,0:21:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My right arm doesn't work anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.54,0:21:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember me?\NI've lost a little weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.84,0:21:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Even I'm pretty darn impressed\Nthat I escaped that inferno alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.47,0:21:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dang, you did shoot me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.99,0:22:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This left hand of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.99,0:22:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not very good at using a pen with it,\Nbut I can shoot a gun just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.42,0:22:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I think I'm gonna kill…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.17,0:22:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,your ex-fiancée, Eva Heinemann.
